**Summary:**

- **Problem:** `packages/frontend/data/genreGearGuides.js` contained 2 fully-built genre gear guide entries (`best-drum-pedals-for-death-metal`, `best-snare-drums-for-thrash-metal`) that were not wired into App.js routes, sitemap.js, or api/meta/[...path].js.
- **Files changed:** Already applied in commits 2f88c84 and 7d090fc, touching `packages/frontend/App.js`, `packages/frontend/components/BeginnerGearGuide.js`, `api/sitemap.js`, and `api/meta/[...path].js`.
- **Fix:** (1) App.js: extended `isBeginnerGuidePage()` and `getBeginnerGuideSlugFromURL()` to detect `/guides/best-[gear]-for-[genre]` URLs via `GENRE_GEAR_GUIDES` lookup; (2) BeginnerGearGuide.js: added genre guide fallback — when slug not in beginner guides, loads from `GENRE_GEAR_GUIDES` and renders Article + FAQPage JSON-LD; (3) sitemap.js: added 2 entries at priority 0.95; (4) api/meta/[...path].js: added genre-guide handler emitting keyword-matched title, Article + FAQPage JSON-LD, and breadcrumbs.
- **Validation:** `node --check` passes on all touched files (exit 0); genre guide slugs are detected in App.js via `GENRE_GEAR_GUIDES` lookup (lines 296-307); sitemap.js emits 2 `/guides/<slug>` entries at priority 0.95 (line 450); SSR meta handler in api/meta/[...path].js returns keyword-matched title + Article + FAQPage JSON-LD for genre guide slugs (lines 596-638).
- **Follow-ups:** Consider adding more genre gear guides (e.g., best cymbals for black metal, best snare for death metal) following the same `GENRE_GEAR_GUIDES` data pattern.
